Colton Folkers also qualified for state competition next week at Kearney with his sixth-place finish at the C-2 district cross country meet in Norfolk on Oct. 15. Also pictured is Taya Skelton, who placed first. 
Fort Calhoun freshman Taya Skelton won the girls Class C-2 district cross country meet in Norfolk this afternoon. 
Colton Folkers of Fort Calhoun also qualified for state competition next week at Kearney with a sixth-place finish in the boys division. 
Fort Calhoun girls team finished in fourth place, and the boys finished fifth. The Arlington boys finished 10th. Tags
